## Vue.js version
2.5.17
## Overview
I have a problem recently.I want to limit the range of numbers entered by the input tag,so I don't want to use v-model directive. When the input box loses focusÔºåI need to check if the number is within reasonable limits.
I wrote the following codeÔºö
```
<input  :value='num' type='text' @change='handleChange' />
data:function(){
  return {
    num:20,   //default value:20
    min: 10 ,
    max:100
  }
},
methods:{
  check(v){
      v=Number(v);
      if(v>=this.max){
         return this.max;
      }else if(v<=this.min){
         return this.min;
      }else{
         return v;
      }
    return this.min;
  },
  handleChange(event){
    this.num=this.check(event.target.value);
    console.log(this.num);
  }
}
```
## Steps
Enter the number randomly in the input box, then move the mouse out of the input box, observe whether the input box number meets the expectations, and observe the console output number.
## Problems
When I input numbers less than 10 for two consecutive times, such as ( 7, 8 ), it was observed that after the first input, the page and console display 10 at the same time, but after the second input, the page displays 8 and the console displays 10.
I originally expected the page and console to display 10 after each input.
